    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-11T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-11T09:00:00-05:00" n="514"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660C.116/161: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cudahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-11T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 11, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 12—3:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. When I called upon Minister for Foreign Affairs March 8, in compliance with
                    the telegraphic instruction No. 10, February 27, he stated that he was not
                    familiar with the matter but that he would cause a preliminary reply to my
                    representations to be sent me on March 11. Foreign Office today reports that
                    Ministry of Commerce has found it impossible to prepare a satisfactory
                    preliminary reply and that it therefore is working on a comprehensive reply
                    which will be sent to Embassy at earliest possible date. See my despatch 624,
                    March 8.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cudahy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
